# QA Audit Fixes — Walkthrough

## Summary
Applied **7 fixes** for all Critical + High issues from the QA audit. Verified **3 reported issues** were false positives (code already handled them). TypeScript build passes with zero errors in changed files.

---

## Issue-by-Issue Fix Log

### ISSUE-001 — Student Fee Page Field Mismatch (Critical)
- **Root Cause:** API returns [StudentFee](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/StudentFee.ts#11-31) model field names (`baseFee`, `discountPct`, `finalFee`) but frontend expects different names (`baseCoursePrice`, `discountPercent`, `finalFees`)
- **Files Changed:** [route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/student/fees/route.ts)
- **Fix:** Remapped API response to frontend-expected field names. Added `discountAmount`, `remainingAmount`, [course](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/fees/course) mapping
- **Verify:** Login as student → navigate to Fee Details → amounts should display correctly

---

### ISSUE-002 — Fee Page Only Shows First Record (High)
- **Root Cause:** Frontend set `d.record` (single record) into state, ignoring `d.fees[]` array
- **Files Changed:** [page.tsx](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/(student)/student/fees/page.tsx)
- **Fix:** Loads all fee records from `fees[]`. Shows tab-like selector buttons when multiple records exist
- **Verify:** Login as student with multiple fee records → all should be switchable

---

### ISSUE-003 — Marks Overwrite Without Confirmation (High)
- **Root Cause:** [handleSave()](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/%28admin%29/admin/jobs/page.tsx#282-293) called immediately on click with no guard
- **Files Changed:** [page.tsx](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/(teacher)/teacher/marks/page.tsx)
- **Fix:** Added `confirm()` dialog showing exam type + student count before saving
- **Verify:** Login as teacher → enter marks → click Save → confirmation dialog should appear

---

### ISSUE-005 — Admin-Created Users Forced to Complete Profile (High)
- **Root Cause:** `isProfileComplete` not set during admin user creation → defaults to `false` → middleware redirects to [/complete-profile](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/complete-profile)
- **Files Changed:** [route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/users/route.ts)
- **Fix:** Added `isProfileComplete: true` to admin-created user objects
- **Verify:** Create student via admin panel → login as that student → should go straight to dashboard

---

### ISSUE-006 — Teacher Has No Test Management Page (High)
- **Root Cause:** API (`/api/admin/tests`) allowed teacher role but no teacher UI existed
- **Files Changed:**
  - [page.tsx](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/(teacher)/teacher/tests/page.tsx) — **NEW**
  - [TeacherSidebar.tsx](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/components/teacher/TeacherSidebar.tsx)
  - [middleware.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/middleware.ts)
- **Fix:** Created teacher tests page, added "MCQ Tests" to sidebar, allowed teacher access to `/api/admin/tests` in middleware
- **Verify:** Login as teacher → sidebar should show "MCQ Tests" → page should list tests

---

### ISSUE-017 — Bulk Fee Assigns to ALL Students Without Batch (High)
- **Root Cause:** `batchId` was optional in the POST handler; omitting it queries ALL active students
- **Files Changed:** [route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/fees/course/route.ts)
- **Fix:** Made `batchId` required. Returns 400 with clear message if missing
- **Verify:** Try bulk fee assignment via API without batchId → should return error

---

### ISSUE-018 — Marks Can Exceed Max Marks (High)
- **Root Cause:** No validation on backend — any numeric value accepted
- **Files Changed:** [route.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/teacher/marks/%5BassignmentId%5D/route.ts)
- **Fix:** Added validation rejecting `marks_obtained > max_marks`, `marks_obtained < 0`, and `max_marks <= 0`
- **Verify:** Try saving marks = 150 with maxMarks = 100 → should return error

